Voxelwise parametric images of microparameters were generated by incorporating the MDIF into the variational Bayesian approach proposed by Castellaro et al. [33]. Specifically for this step, the k-means clustering algorithm described above was used to generate a functional atlas containing 40 clusters for each subject: 20 GM, 10 WM and 10 non-brain clusters, the latter including cerebrospinal fluid and voxels surrounding the brain. In the variational Bayesian fitting routine, each cluster TAC was fit to the irreversible 2TCM solution, with its rate constants used as priors for all intra-cluster voxels assuming a Gaussian distribution of possible values. Parametric maps of CMRGlu were computed from \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
